STEP 03: Select only the necessary continuous variables

dataset03 <- dataset03 %>%
  select(num_range("item_", 1:87, width = 2)) %>%  # item_01 ... item_87
  select(where(is.numeric))                         # keep continuous only

STEP 04. EFA with lavaan, testing factors from 1 to 7, per recommendation by earlier parallel analysis

dataset03_lavaan <- efa(data = dataset03 [,1:87], rotation = "oblimin", nfactors = 1:7)

STEP 07. Remove items with low loading, low communality, high complexity. Then save as a new dataset.

remove_items <- c(
  "item_01","item_32","item_51","item_57","item_38",
  "item_87","item_33","item_46","item_23","item_45","item_52")
# keep only items that actually exist (prevents errors)
remove_items <- intersect(remove_items, names(dataset03))
# create new dataset
dataset04 <- dataset03[, !names(dataset03) %in% remove_items]
# save as a new csv
write.csv(dataset04, "lar-china_test03_group_A_622_v0.csv", row.names = FALSE)
